# Technical Architecture Decisions

**Project:** HR Attrition & Workforce Analytics Platform

**Version:** 1.0

**Document Type:** Architecture Decision Record (ADR)

**Status:** Final

---

# 1. Purpose

This document explains the key architectural decisions made during the design and implementation of the HR Attrition & Workforce Analytics Platform.

Unlike the High-Level Design (HLD), Low-Level Design (LLD), and Data Architecture documents—which describe **how** the system works—this document explains **why** specific technologies, patterns, and design approaches were selected.

The objective is to document architectural trade-offs, design constraints, and future scalability considerations.

---

# 2. System Scope

The platform is designed as a **local, batch-oriented Business Intelligence solution**.

It is intended for portfolio demonstration and analytical reporting rather than continuous production operations.

### System Boundary

```mermaid
flowchart LR

A[Raw HR Dataset]

B[Python ETL]

C[SQLite Warehouse]

D[Power BI Dashboard]

E[Business Reports]

F[HR Stakeholders]

A --> B
B --> C
C --> D
D --> E
E --> F
```

Within the current scope:

- No external APIs
- No cloud infrastructure
- No scheduled execution
- No streaming data
- No multi-user architecture

All processing occurs locally against a static HR dataset.

---

# 3. Architecture Principles

The platform follows several guiding principles.

### Simplicity

The solution minimizes unnecessary complexity while maintaining enterprise design practices.

---

### Reproducibility

All analytical outputs can be reproduced from the original dataset through deterministic ETL and SQL processing.

---

### Modularity

Python, SQL, and Power BI responsibilities are separated into independent layers to improve maintainability.

---

### Single Source of Truth

Business KPIs are generated within the SQL analytical layer and validated before visualization.

---

### Documentation First

Every architectural decision is supported by technical documentation, ensuring maintainability and transparency.

