# 5. Trade-Off Analysis

| Decision | Benefit | Trade-Off |
|----------|---------|-----------|
| Python ETL | Flexible and reproducible | Requires Python runtime |
| SQLite | Lightweight and portable | Not intended for enterprise-scale workloads |
| Star Schema | High analytical performance | Additional modeling effort |
| SQL KPI Layer | Centralized business logic | Additional SQL maintenance |
| Manual Pipeline | Simplicity | No automated scheduling |
| Local Execution | Easy setup | No collaborative deployment |

---

# 6. Enterprise-Scale Architecture

If deployed in a production enterprise environment, the architecture could be extended as follows:

```text
HRIS (Workday / SAP SuccessFactors)

↓

Azure Data Factory / Airflow

↓

Azure SQL / Snowflake

↓

dbt Models

↓

Power BI Service

↓

Business Users
```

Potential enterprise enhancements include:

- Automated data ingestion
- Incremental ETL processing
- Cloud-hosted analytical warehouse
- Scheduled pipeline execution
- Power BI Service deployment
- Row-Level Security (RLS)
- CI/CD deployment pipelines
- Automated KPI reconciliation

---

# 7. Architecture Constraints

The current implementation intentionally operates within the following constraints:

| Constraint | Reason |
|------------|--------|
| Static HR dataset | No live HRIS connection available |
| Local execution | Portfolio project scope |
| Single-user workflow | Demonstration environment |
| Batch processing | No continuous data updates |
| Snapshot analytics | Dataset contains no historical dates |

These constraints are design choices based on project scope rather than technical limitations.

